Text.SourceString: You’re going to be a farmer, huh?//<portrait=annoyed>What brings you out here, then?//<portrait=normal>By the way, you can call me <NPCName>Paul</>.
The docuseries Friends with Wildlife? Yeah!//<portrait=normal>My wife and I made that! I can’t believe you know about it.//Cool, cool! Very cool.
Maybe I’ll plant cauliflower in our backyard. Hmm…
You’ve seen our backyard, right?//Is the environment too harsh for cauliflower, you think?
There are rats and snakes around the dumpster, but I don’t think other wild animals go near it.
It’s too close to town. So many people in one place scare off the wildlife.
Think you could give me some gardening tips? Let’s say I want to plant some carrots…
What have you got up your sleeve? Come on, don’t be shy.
Think you could give me some gardening tips? Let’s say I want to plant some carrots…
What have you got up your sleeve? Come on, don’t be shy.
There are rats and snakes around the dumpster, but I don’t think other wild animals go near it.
It’s too close to town. So many people in one place scare off the wildlife.
I have to do the recycling today. I completely forgot about that.

Humph… I’ll just do it tomorrow.//<portrait=normal>I don’t think <NPCName>Anne</>
will notice.
The town seems much cleaner lately, for some reason.//Have you noticed that?
What a weekend! I was glad for a break, but… Phew! I’m glad it’s over.//<portrait=normal>I love dancing, but my hips weren’t made for dancing, I can tell you that much.
I’m refreshed and ready to get back to work!
Ah, your farm – something is going on over there, <PlayerName>$player</>.//<portrait=annoyed>Nothing spooky, but…
I’m sure some unusual creatures live on that side of the island.//I don’t have any footage, though.
Ah, your farm – something is going on over there, <PlayerName>$player</>.//<portrait=annoyed>Nothing spooky, but…
I’m sure some unusual creatures live on that side of the island.//I don’t have any footage, though.
It’s only the beginning of the week, and we’ve already recorded some rare birds.
This is my week.//This week is going to be a doozy, I can tell!
Try not to spook the wildlife when you go in the forest, will ya?
This may come as a surprise, but making a wildlife documentary is mostly just waiting around.//Not a lot of action… The narration, though. That’s a different beast altogether.
Sometimes I wait for weeks and don’t get any usable footage at all.
What a day, eh?
I think I’ll go down to the tavern tomorrow. It’ll be a great excuse to put my dancing shoes on.
It’ll be nice to see <NPCName>Frank</> too.
I’m having fun. I mean, it’s Saturday, and I’m spending time with the family!//<portrait=normal>What else are we gonna do today but have fun?
I wouldn’t mind editing some video, but <NPCName>Anne</> said it can wait.//So we’ll wait.
I saw that cute little puppy chasing birds in town yesterday.
Ah, <NPCName>Taco</>!//That’s the name. Yes.
What are you up to this week? You always seem to be busy and running around all the time.//What a life you must have, eh?
Have you started farming this season?
Don’t stay up too late, will ya? It happened to me one time, working late editing footage of a cassowary.//It didn’t end well.
I passed out and had to be taken to the hospital.
I saw that cute little puppy chasing birds in town yesterday.
Ah, <NPCName>Taco</>!//That’s the name. Yes.
I can’t sit around at home for too long. I get bored easily and want to go make something of my day.
Well, not just at home… I don’t like being confined in general.//<portrait=normal>It scrambles my brain.
Don’t stay up too late, will ya? It happened to me one time, working late editing footage of a cassowary.//It didn’t end well.
I passed out and had to be taken to the hospital.
Cassowaries can be very dangerous if they feel threatened. I’m always very careful when I spot one.
Yeah, it’s the same way with a lot of animals.//They’re beautiful creatures, and we have to be careful not to harm them. They have feelings, too.
I have footage of this massive green sawfish. I’ll have to show you sometime!
I didn’t swim close to it. <NPCName>Anne</> and I were diving, and she happened to have a video camera on her. Lucky!
It would be an exciting project to just camp out at your farm and see what wildlife we can find.
As long as you’re cool with it, of course.
Whoa! <PlayerName>$player</>!
Phew. That was a heck of a surprise.
Whoa! <PlayerName>$player</>!
Phew. That was a heck of a surprise.
It would be an exciting project to just camp out at your farm and see what wildlife we can find.
As long as you’re cool with it, of course.
It was <NPCName>Anne</>’s idea to make informative videos for kids, too… Made quite a bit from it, actually.//She thinks about stuff like that. She’s a very outside-the-box type.
Yeah, the videos are about wildlife, of course. We made them easy for kids to understand.
We made some videos for <NPCName>Zoe</> when she was younger, to teach her about wildlife.//We weren’t thinking then that other kids would like them, too!

Well, <NPCName>Anne</> did, actually.//<portrait=normal>Then we sold a few, and they were surprisingly successful, so we made more. But now that <NPCName>Zoe</>’s a bit older, we kind of stopped making them.

Yeah, it’s the same way with a lot of animals.//They’re beautiful creatures, and we have to be careful not to harm them. They have feelings, too.
<NPCName>Zoe</> is too young to go to the tavern. It’s very loud, and there’s alcohol and drunk people everywhere.//Just not ideal for kids.
Besides, it’s probably healthier for her to eat at home, where we know where all the ingredients came from.//Though indulging every now and then can’t be too bad, can it?
<NPCName>Zoe</> is too young to go to the tavern. It’s very loud, and there’s alcohol and drunk people everywhere.//Just not ideal for kids.
Besides, she has school tomorrow.//She won’t be able to wake up on time if she stays up late.
We made some videos for <NPCName>Zoe</> when she was younger, to teach her about wildlife.//We weren’t thinking then that other kids would like them, too!

Well, <NPCName>Anne</> did, actually.//<portrait=normal>Then we sold a few, and they were surprisingly successful, so we made more. But now that <NPCName>Zoe</>’s a bit older, we kind of stopped making them.
Cauliflower season, isn’t it? Yeah, I should know.//I used to be obsessed with growing it. My mom’s favorite vegetable.
I don’t like it that much anymore.
It’s still a bit chilly out, so I think some animals are still hibernating.
I was expecting to see way more frogs and bees this time of year.//Hmm…
I was expecting to see way more frogs and bees this time of year.//Hmm…
Watch your step, <PlayerName>$player</>. As the weather gets warmer, more animals will come out of hibernation.
Watch your step, <PlayerName>$player</>. As the weather gets warmer, you may find snakes in the forest.
Try not to step on them!
We planted strawberries one time for <NPCName>Zoe</>’s school project. It was fun.//We shared the harvest with some wild animals.
It was a rewarding project, and it taught kids the cycle of life firsthand.
<NPCName>Zoe</> had a school project where we planted strawberries one time. It was fun.//We shared the harvest with some wild animals.
It was a rewarding project, and it teaches kids the cycle of life firsthand.
Planting bananas around the lake may not be a bad idea. Wildlife could take advantage of them as well.
The thing about planting in the wild is so much wildlife comes out at night.//The seedlings would probably be gone the next day.
Planting bananas around the lake may not be a bad idea. Wildlife could take advantage of them as well.
The thing about planting in the wild is so much wildlife comes out at night.//The seedlings would probably be gone the next day.
Do you think we should plant more trees to shelter wildlife?
I knew you’d think so! Shelter isn’t just for rain, you know. It’s important on sunny days too. Just like us, animals don’t want to overheat.
Thankfully, most of the trees here are renewables.//And the fact that we plant more trees every year has really helped the environment.
There’s a certain part of this island we don’t touch at all, and I’m glad for the restriction.
Hopefully, we can teach our kids to respect wildlife and to reserve some space only for them.
There’s a certain part of this island we don’t touch at all, and I’m glad for the restriction.
Hopefully, we can teach our kids to respect wildlife and to reserve some space only for them.
Winter, eh? Less work for me and you. There are significantly fewer animals out and about this time of year.
Your animals are okay, I hope? It can get really cold in the barn.//I’d get one of those warmer machines if I were you.
Ah, yes, yes! Heaters. I forgot the proper name for them for a split second there.//<portrait=normal>Must be my Winter brain coming back.
Your animals are okay, I hope? It can get really cold in the barn.//I’d get one of those warmer machines if I were you.
Ah, yes, yes! Heaters. I forgot the proper name for them for a split second there.//<portrait=normal>Must be my Winter brain coming back.
Oh my, it’s almost the twentieth.//I haven’t bought anything for my wedding anniversary yet.
You don’t know where to get sunflowers this time of year, do you? They’re <NPCName>Anne</>’s favorite.
Maybe <NPCName>Ben</> might have some… Hmm… Let’s hope so.
Oh my, it’s almost the twentieth.//I haven’t bought anything for my wedding anniversary yet.
You don’t know where to get sunflowers this time of year, do you? They’re <NPCName>Anne</>’s favorite.
Maybe <NPCName>Ben</> might have some… Hmm… Let’s hope so.
I’m beginning to miss fresh strawberries. Hmm…
We’ve been enjoying building snowmen this Winter. I think <NPCName>Zoe</> had a lot of fun.
Don’t let the rain stop you, <PlayerName>$player</>.
You wanna go and mine? You go and mine, fella!//<portrait=normal>The island is your oyster.
What are we doing indoors? We should be out there in nature. In the rain!
My wife has been saying how humid it is lately. And I agree!//Even when it rains like this, eh?
My wife has been saying how humid it is lately. And I agree!
Don’t let the rain stop you, <PlayerName>$player</>.
You wanna go and mine? You go and mine, fella!//<portrait=normal>The island is your oyster.
Or maybe wait until tomorrow.//It’s getting pretty late.
Good night!
Don’t let the storm stop you, <PlayerName>$player</>.
You wanna go and mine? You go and mine, fella!//<portrait=normal>The island is your oyster.
What are we doing indoor? We should be out there in nature. In the rain!
Great weather. Great weather, indeed. Keeping my hat on, though!
I’m going to go out on a limb and say the animals are happy too today.//They like sunny days as much as we do.
It’s snowing outside, isn’t it?
Either that or you really need um… Never mind.
Don’t let the snow stop you, <PlayerName>$player</>.
You wanna go and mine? You go and mine, fella!//<portrait=normal>The island is your oyster.

You wanna go and mine? You go and mine, fella!//<portrait=normal>The island is your oyster.
Great weather. Great weather, indeed.
That’s why I’m out here, <PlayerName>$player</>. Why else?
Great weather. Great weather, indeed.
That’s why I’m out here, <PlayerName>$player</>. Why else?
Psst…
I’m trying to capture footage… Will you keep your voice down, please?
I’m at the lake a lot. It's my job.//Gotta go where my job takes me. Seems like you are too, huh?
What are you doing here this time of day, anyway?
I saw a couple of monkeys taking a bath in the lake the other day. It’s pretty hard to predict when they’ll be out.
I don’t want to get too close to them. It’s their home. I don’t want to invade.
Uh… I don’t know who comes here on weekends. I usually spend mine at the beach.
But I’m here pretty much throughout the week, if that means anything to you.
I just finished editing last week’s footage. Everything is coming along great! Now onto the fun stuff.
Well, yeah. My wife does most of the editing. She likes it.
It’s tough to get footage of the corpse flower. The plant doesn’t flower often.
I know it’s technically a plant, but it’s rare, huh? People love to see it. We certainly do.
<PlayerName>$player</>! Great to see you here, my friend.//Are you here to see some animal footage we got yesterday?
HEY! <NPCName>Anne</>! We have a guest!
I don’t see you here very often, <PlayerName>$player</>. I hope things are okay back at the farm.
I was looking at a space back there to put a small pet house, maybe. Not for a pet, but shelter for wild animals.
Some of the bulbs on our porch burned out. Be careful going home, okay?
I haven’t had time to change them. We don’t get visitors often anyway.//Besides, wildlife doesn’t like a lot of light at night.
Sweating the day away, <PlayerName>$player</>? I’m playing volleyball with the family.//<portrait=happy>Trying to see see if I can still beat my wife at it.
Come on, <NPCName>Zoe</>! Let’s see who the winners are!
You can always dive into the ocean if it gets too hot.//Cool down a bit, eh? Don’t overheat!
Keep your hat handy!
We get to see seals and all kinds of fish here. Sometimes turtles come to the shore, but not very often.//So keep an eye out.
A couple of <NPCName>Zoe</>’s friends live around here. She always has a lot of fun at the beach.
Oh, ho, ho, ho! <PlayerName>$player</>!
Did we talk? Really? Ah, must be the music then. It’s so loud; I can’t seem to focus. Apologies.

And then the bear was behind me all along! That was scary. Very very scary... Forest can be scary at times.//But of course, I had to keep calm. <NPCName>Anne</> was with me... Don't want to spook the bear.//We stayed inside the tent the whole night.
What in the world is this song? Do you think <NPCName>Theo</> wrote it himself?
It’s certainly one of a kind! Let’s dance to it!
